Learn to Love Lambdas
by Jeremy Clark
www.jeremybytes.com

1. Parameter(s)
2. => "goes to" operator
3. Expression or Statement(s)

Anonymous Delegate

2 different types of lambdas

Expression Lambda
  (Person p) => p.FirstName == "John"

Statement Lambda
  Perform some kind of action, but don't return a value.
  (object sender, EventArgs e) =>
   {
       ListBox.ItemsSorce = e.Result;
       Console.WriteLine("Hello");
   }

Variations
	Optional Param Types (Parameter Type Inference)
	 (sender, e) => {
	     ListBox.ItemSource = e.Result; }
	
	Optional Parens for Single Parameter
	e => {Console.Write(e.ToString()); }
	
	Optional Braces for Single Expressions
	p => p.Name == "John"
	
	Empty Parens for No Parameter
	() => { Console.Write("John"); }


